HEADWORD: Bolognese
<hw>Bo*lo`gnese"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to Bologna.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A native of
Bologna.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bolognese school</b></col> <fld>(Paint.)</fld>, <cd>a
school of painting founded by the Carracci, otherwise called the Lombard
or Eclectic school, the object of which was to unite the excellences of
the preceding schools.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bolognian</ent>⟦br⟧
